        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 2:43PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Bagwell, or 11 miles west of Clarksville, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Bogata, Bagwell and Detroit.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
